-------------- SQS: Pull model ------------------------
Java Integration: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=smR8TYzBE4s
- Highly scalable
- low cost

Two types:
1. Standard = at least one delivery, no ordering, unlimited throughput 
2. FIFO = First in First out, exactly once processing, low throughput

How to choose: Standard if throughput is important, FIFO if order is important.

- Producer receives unique message id after putting the message in the queue
- If one consumer is consuming the message along with receipt handle XYZ other consumer cannot consume it. After successfully consuming the
message it deletes it using receipt handle XYZ.
- Consumer has to process the message in expiry visibility time. Otherwise it goes to ready state.
- After specfic number of processed failures the  message goes to Dead Letter Queue from ready queue.
- Other AWS resources can access SQS using IAM roles like EC2 -> SQS
- User has to configure SQS access policy to provide access to other accounts.

Ques: How to reduce number of API calls to SQS ?
Ans: Use LongPolling - When looking for messages you can specficy waitTimeSeconds upto 20 seconds.

Ques: How about messages lost ?
Ans: Maximum retention period = 4 days, max = 14 days.

Ques: What is the best practice to give high priority to premium customers in SQS ?
Ans: Create two queues - one for free customers and one for premium customers.

